* ============================================================
*  TABLE-BUFFER WAL — PHASE B RECOVERY VERIFY (reopen after "crash")
*
*  Purpose: USE WALREC after the runner turned the .tbj into a committed log.
*           Recovery-on-open must replay the redo record, so recno 1 NAME becomes
*           "Recovered", and the .tbj must be removed. Then clean up.
* ============================================================
SET ECHO OFF
SET TIMER ON
SET TALK ON

SET PATH DBF DBF/pinocchio

ECHO --- USE triggers recovery of the committed .tbj (expect a recovered notice) ---
USE WALREC
GO 1
ECHO --- recno 1 NAME should now be Recovered (replayed from the committed .tbj) ---
DISPLAY

ECHO --- cleanup ---
TABLE BUFFER OFF
CLOSE
ERASE TABLE WALREC CONFIRM

ECHO ============================================================
ECHO WAL PHASE B VERIFY COMPLETE. Confirm:
ECHO   USE printed "recovered a committed table-buffer journal (.tbj)".
ECHO   recno 1 NAME = Recovered (redo replayed on open).
ECHO ============================================================
